flowchart LR

accTitle: IA-005 — Motion to Effect Flow
accDescr: Signal pipeline from raw motion feed through semantic derivation and normalized control contract to rendered mosaic behavior

classDef input   fill:#0F2A1F,stroke:#59D98E,stroke-width:2px,color:#E9FFF2,font-weight:bold;
classDef process fill:#2B1742,stroke:#B78CFF,stroke-width:2px,color:#F5EEFF,font-weight:bold;
classDef control fill:#33240D,stroke:#FFB347,stroke-width:2px,color:#FFF4E5,font-weight:bold;
classDef runtime fill:#2A1020,stroke:#FF79C6,stroke-width:2px,color:#FFEAF7,font-weight:bold;
classDef output  fill:#132B2A,stroke:#66E0D1,stroke-width:2px,color:#EDFFFC,font-weight:bold;
classDef guide   fill:#1A1A2E,stroke:#C8CDD8,stroke-width:1.5px,color:#F3F5F7,font-style:italic;

RMF(["Raw Motion Feed\nCV pose stream · unfiltered"]):::input
VSS["Validate · Smooth · Stabilize\nOutlier rejection · temporal smoothing · confidence gate"]:::process
DIS["Derived Interaction Signals\nPresence · zone · energy · approach vector"]:::process
NCC["Normalized Control Contract\n0..1 typed named values · stable frame-to-frame"]:::control
RCA["Response Curves · Artistic Gains\nCurve-shaped · per-effect gain staging"]:::control
MIP["Material + Instance Parameters\nMPC write · DMI override · per-instance push"]:::runtime
RMB(["Rendered Mosaic Behavior\nFinal per-frame visual state"]):::output

subgraph CONSTRAINTS [" Pipeline Constraints "]
    PC1["Raw CV data must not reach effects directly\nAll wiring passes through the control contract"]:::process
    PC2["Contract values are 0..1 normalized\nEffect systems apply their own gain shaping"]:::control
    PC3["Smoothing applied before contract publish\nHysteresis prevents frame-level flicker"]:::process
end

GID>"2026 pattern: derive compact semantic contract — never wire raw CV data directly into effects"]:::guide

RMF -->|raw pose · velocity| VSS
VSS -->|cleaned signal| DIS
DIS -->|presence · zone · energy| NCC
NCC -->|0..1 normalized| RCA
RCA -->|shaped values| MIP
MIP -->|param push| RMB

VSS -.->|enforces| PC3
NCC -.->|enforces| PC2
DIS -.->|enforces| PC1

